Rating: 0
These are yummy! I make them ahead (don't bake them first) and freeze them on a cookie sheet until frozen, then store them in a container in the freezer to have on hand for impromptu gatherings. You can pop them in the oven and they are fantastic! I sometimes add a tablespoon of pesto--give a nice green color and a little different twist. Only use the best parm, freshly grated--asiago is good too!

Rating: 4
I made these for a baby shower and they were wonderful! I used green onion to add some color and doubled the cayenne pepper for a bit more spice. I baked them prior to atending the shower, so I was a little concerned that they would not be as good as when they are served fresh out of the oven, but they were still great! They are so quick and easy to make and I loved the fact that I didn't have to go out and buy a bunch of expensive, hard to find ingredients. I would definitely recommend buying the Parmigiano-Reggiano and grating it yourself. I gave the recipe to a friend and she used some pre-grated cheese, and said they were not nearly as good.

