Rating: 0
I haven't tried this yet, however here is a recipe I have been making for over 25 years that is similar...with a different take on it...you will love this. Ingredience: 1 small size loaf of cocktail bread (I use rye), 1/2 lb grated sharp cheddar cheese, 1/2 onion chopped, 1/2 c. mayonaise, 1 raw egg, pinch of dried parsley,thyme,red pepper or cayenne,paprika. Mix together and spread on bread rounds, then put under the broiler til cheese melts. I always made a double batch, because they go like hot cakes...people love them and the mix can be made ahead of time and is good for several days. Enjoy!

