Rating: 4
This is an old family tradition - we call them "cheesy breads". I generally use thinly-sliced baguette as the bread. The combination is so fantastic. I love serving them because everyone goes ga-ga over them. When I tell them the base is Mayonnaise they are surprised and take another one. You can also put little bay shrimp into the mixture.